---
import Callout from "@plugdash/callout/Callout.astro";
import InstallCommand from "../../components/InstallCommand.astro";
import PluginReference from "../../components/PluginReference.astro";
import { demoPost, pluginDocToc } from "../../data/demoPost";
import { getPlugin } from "../../data/plugins";
import Doc from "../../layouts/Doc.astro";

const plugin = getPlugin("callout")!;
---

<Doc
  tocEntries={pluginDocToc}
  currentSlug="callout"
  readingTimeMinutes={2}
  wordCount={240}
  title="callout"
  section="@plugdash/callout"
  description="Info, warning, tip, and danger blocks for the EmDash editor."
>
  <h2 id="what-it-does">What it does</h2>
  <p>
    Registers a <code>callout</code> block type in the EmDash Portable
    Text editor. Authors pick one of four variants - info, warning, tip,
    danger - and optionally add a title. Ships
    <code>Callout.astro</code> for rendering in your theme.
  </p>
  <p>
    callout is a Native plugin (it registers an editor block) - it runs
    unsandboxed.
  </p>

  <Callout variant="tip" title="Tip">
    <p>Use the tip variant for the non-obvious thing that makes a task
    easier. This block is the plugin rendering itself on its own doc page.</p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="install">Install</h2>
  <InstallCommand command={plugin.installCommand} />

  <h2 id="register">Register</h2>
  <p>
    Open <code>astro.config.mjs</code> at the root of your Astro project.
    Import the plugin at the top, then add it to the <code>plugins</code>
    array of the <code>emdash()</code> integration - the one that sits
    inside Astro's top-level <code>integrations</code> array:
  </p>
  <pre><code>{`// astro.config.mjs
import { defineConfig } from "astro/config"
import emdash from "emdash/astro"
import { calloutPlugin } from "@plugdash/callout"

export default defineConfig({
  integrations: [
    emdash({
      plugins: [calloutPlugin()],
    }),
  ],
})`}</code></pre>

  <h2 id="add-the-component">Add the component</h2>
  <p>Use the component in your Portable Text renderer for blocks with
  <code>_type === "callout"</code>:</p>
  <pre><code>{`import Callout from "@plugdash/callout/Callout.astro"
<Callout variant="info" title="Heads up">
  <p>Content goes here.</p>
</Callout>`}</code></pre>

  <h2 id="live-demo">Live demo</h2>
  <div class="demo-inline" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.75rem">
    <Callout variant="info" title="Info">
      <p>Background context readers might want but don't strictly need.</p>
    </Callout>
    <Callout variant="warning" title="Warning">
      <p>Something that will bite them if they skip it.</p>
    </Callout>
    <Callout variant="danger" title="Danger">
      <p>Something that will break things if they get it wrong.</p>
    </Callout>
  </div>

  <PluginReference plugin={plugin} />

  <h2 id="for-agents">For agents</h2>
  <p>After install, open the EmDash admin editor and confirm the
  <code>callout</code> block type appears in the block menu. The plugin
  does not write metadata - it only registers the block type.</p>
</Doc>
